### Important: Tailwind v4 Setup
Base44 scaffolds Tailwind v3. Always upgrade:
```bash
npm uninstall tailwindcss autoprefixer postcss
npm install tailwindcss@latest @tailwindcss/postcss postcss
rm -f tailwind.config.js
```
**NEVER** use `@tailwindcss/vite` — it breaks custom `@theme` colors. Use PostCSS only:
```js
// postcss.config.js
export default { plugins: { '@tailwindcss/postcss': {} } };
```

## Architecture
- One component per file, max 150 lines
- Extract hooks to `hooks/`, utilities to `lib/`
- Use `React.lazy` + `Suspense` for heavy sections (3D, galleries)
- Components: PascalCase (`HeroScene.tsx`)
- Hooks: `use` prefix (`useScrollProgress.ts`)

## Code Quality
- No `any` — use proper types or generics
- Cleanup all GSAP contexts and Lenis instances in `useEffect` return
- `cursor-pointer` on all clickable elements
- No emojis as UI icons — use Lucide React SVGs

## Core Principle: Tools Adapt, Never Disappear

Our skills (`premium-effects`, `scroll-kinetics`, `3d-scenes`) are the professional engine — they deliver studio-quality components, animations, and effects. They are ALWAYS available. They NEVER get blanket-disabled.

What changes per project is their **configuration** — colors, speeds, densities, intensities, font choices — derived from the brief. A SparklesCore on a wellness site uses warm gold particles at low density (30, speed 0.2). The same SparklesCore on a tech site uses electric blue at high density (100, speed 0.6). Same tool, different tuning.

### Override Hierarchy (highest wins)

```
1. Client brief / user instructions     ← ALWAYS wins. Specific colors, fonts, "I want X" requests.
2. Style archetype DNA                  ← Industry-tuned defaults. Configures tools, suggests intensity.
3. ui-ux-pro-max output                 ← Data-driven recommendations. Baseline when no archetype matches.
```

When the client specifies colors, fonts, or specific preferences — ALL tools adapt to those values. The archetype provides smart defaults for anything the client didn't specify. ui-ux-pro-max fills remaining gaps.

### How Archetypes Configure Tools

Archetypes do NOT forbid tools. They **tune** them for the industry:

| Instead of... | The archetype says... |
|---------------|----------------------|
| "SKIP SparklesCore" | "SparklesCore: density=30, speed=0.15, warm gold particles — barely visible, atmospheric" |
| "SKIP ShimmerButton" | "CTA style: soft pill shape, muted fill — ShimmerButton with `shimmerColor` at 5% opacity, or simple solid button" |
| "SKIP InfiniteMarquee" | "Kinetic: very slow (speed=50+), subtle opacity (0.3), or replace with static decorative separator" |
| "SKIP BorderBeam" | "Borders: duration=14s, very faint colors (5% opacity) — barely perceptible, or simple CSS border" |

The Design Blueprint decides the final configuration per section. When the archetype recommends REPLACING an effect with a simpler alternative, that is the smart default — but the client can always override.

## Minimum Visual Quality Bar

The quality bar is split into two tiers. **Base Tier** is mandatory for every project. **Enhancement Tier** is always ON — archetypes and brief configure HOW each pattern manifests (intensity, style, colors), not WHETHER it exists.

### Base Tier (ALWAYS required — no exceptions)

| # | Pattern | Requirement |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 1 | Section labels | Small colored text above every non-hero heading |
| 2 | Letter-spaced headings | `letter-spacing` on major display headings (0.1em+ default, archetype may specify less) |
| 3 | Scroll animations | EVERY section has a scroll-triggered entrance animation |
| 4 | Smooth scroll | Lenis active and synced with GSAP ScrollTrigger |
| 5 | Scroll progress | Thin gradient bar at top of page showing scroll position |
| 6 | Animated backgrounds | Gradient blobs or decorative elements in hero + at least 1 more section |
| 7 | Button hierarchy | Primary (solid), secondary (outline), WhatsApp (green) — all `min-h-[48px]` |
| 8 | Consistent centering | All content uses `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8` |
| 9 | Complete footer | Contact links, social icons, copyright, back-to-top button |
| 10 | WhatsApp FAB | Sticky bottom-start with pulse animation |

### Enhancement Tier (ALWAYS present — archetype configures intensity & style)

Every pattern below exists in every project. The archetype determines **how** it manifests — from full intensity (Bold Agency) to barely-there subtlety (Wellness Clean). The Design Blueprint maps the final configuration.

| # | Pattern | High intensity (agency/tech) | Low intensity (wellness/professional) |
|---|---------|----------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| 11 | Gradient text | Vivid multi-color gradients on headings | Subtle warm gradient on one accent line, or solid color with slight tonal shift |
| 12 | Card treatment | Full glassmorphism with backdrop-blur | Soft background cards with minimal shadow |
| 13 | Card borders | BorderBeam with electric colors, 6s speed | Very faint border (14s, 3% opacity) or clean CSS border |
| 14 | Card interaction | ThreeDCard with intensity 12+ | ThreeDCard intensity 3-4 (barely perceptible tilt) or `translateY(-2px)` hover |
| 15 | CTA style | ShimmerButton with bright sweep | ShimmerButton with 5% shimmerColor (almost invisible sweep), or solid fill |
| 16 | Section atmosphere | SparklesCore density=100, Spotlight, LampEffect | SparklesCore density=20 in warm gold, or gradient blobs only |
| 17 | Kinetic dividers | InfiniteMarquee speed=15, ParallaxText velocity=5 | InfiniteMarquee speed=50+ at 30% opacity, or decorative icon separator |
| 18 | Flowing depth | FlowingBackground opacity=0.06, outlined text | FlowingBackground opacity=0.02 (barely visible), or alternating bg/bg-alt |

## Performance Targets
- LCP ≤ 2.5s — preload hero images/fonts, inline critical CSS
- INP ≤ 200ms — never block main thread > 50ms
- CLS ≤ 0.1 — explicit width/height on images and embeds
- Animate ONLY `transform` and `opacity` (GPU-composited)
- Total page weight < 1.5MB
- Images: AVIF > WebP > JPEG with `<picture>` fallback

### JS Budget (gzipped, initial load)

| Page type | Budget | Mandatory technique |
|-----------|--------|---------------------|
| Without 3D scenes | < 200kb | Standard code-splitting |
| With 3D scenes | < 300kb | `React.lazy` + `Suspense` for ALL 3D components, static fallback on mobile |

Three.js alone is ~150kb. If using 3D, lazy-load is non-negotiable. If the page can achieve its goals without 3D, prefer 2D effects from `premium-effects` and `scroll-kinetics`.

## Mobile First
- Design mobile-first, enhance for desktop
- Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:640` `md:768` `lg:1024` `xl:1280`
- Min tap target: 44×44px with 8px spacing between adjacent targets
- Primary CTAs in bottom 1/3 of screen (thumb zone)
- Use `clamp()` for fluid typography: `clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 2rem)`
- Disable custom cursor effects on touch devices
- Simplify heavy animations on mobile (`gsap.matchMedia()`)
- `overflow-x: hidden` on body — prevent horizontal scroll
- Replace pinned scrollytelling with vertical card stacks on mobile

## RTL / Hebrew Rules
- `<html lang="he" dir="rtl">` in index.html
- Tailwind logical properties: `start/end` not `left/right`, `ms-/me-` not `ml-/mr-`
- NEVER use SplitType or GSAP SplitText for Hebrew — use Framer Motion KineticText
- Gender-neutral CTAs: infinitive verbs ("להתחיל", "לרכוש", not "התחילי")
- `word-break: keep-all` globally — prevents Hebrew breaking mid-word
- Hero text: separate `clamp()` per line + `whitespace-nowrap`
- CTA arrows: use `ArrowLeft` (not ArrowRight) in RTL
- Carousel: `opts={{ direction: 'rtl' }}`
- **RTL `<select>` dropdowns:** Browser default arrow renders on the wrong side. Use `appearance-none` + custom Lucide `ChevronDown` icon positioned with `end-4` and `pe-12` padding:
  ```tsx
  <div className="relative">
    <select className="w-full appearance-none pe-12 ps-5 ...">
      <option>...</option>
    </select>
    <ChevronDown className="absolute end-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-5 h-5 pointer-events-none" />
  </div>
  ```
- **InfiniteMarquee in RTL:** Wrap `react-fast-marquee` with `dir="ltr"` + `unicodeBidi: 'isolate'` on outer div, inner content uses `dir="rtl"` to preserve Hebrew text direction

## Lessons Learned — Library & Pattern Warnings

### NEVER use these libraries
| Library | Problem | Use instead |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| `liquid-glass-react` | SVG filter containers break flex/grid layouts (especially navbars). Requires React 19+. Adds ~50kb. | Custom `liquid-glass-dark`/`liquid-glass-light` CSS classes (see `premium-effects` skill) |
| Custom CSS marquee (`translateX(-50%)` + 2 copies) | Fails when content is narrower than viewport — creates visible gaps where text disappears | `react-fast-marquee` with `autoFill` (see `scroll-kinetics` skill) |

### Animation flickering prevention
- **Gallery sections with filtering:** NEVER use Framer Motion `layout` prop or `AnimatePresence mode="popLayout"` on gallery items — causes severe flickering during filter transitions. Use CSS transitions instead.
- **Contact/form sections:** NEVER wrap form sections with `ScrollReveal` that sets `initial={{ opacity: 0 }}` — causes flash-of-invisible-content on mobile. Render forms immediately.
- **Image preloading:** For gallery sections, preload all images BEFORE they enter the viewport using a custom `usePreloadImages` hook to prevent layout-shift flickering.

### Decorative effects — use only when the brief/archetype calls for them
- **DecorativeShapes:** Replaces FloatingOrbs. 11 shape types (orb, star, sparkle, heart, leaf, petal, diamond, hexagon, triangle, ring, dot). Choose shapes that match the industry (hearts+stars for kids, leaves+petals for wellness, hexagons+triangles for tech). Max 2 sections per page, 8-12 count desktop, start with `speed="slow"`. NOT for corporate, legal, medical — skip entirely.
- **Liquid Glass CSS:** Only for projects that need glossy/glass finishes (luxury, boutique, beauty, high-end agency). Minimalist, corporate, and clean archetypes should use flat or subtle shadow treatments.
- **SparklesCore:** Add `IntersectionObserver` to pause when off-screen. Cap `devicePixelRatio` at 2. Debounce resize events.
- **ThreeDCard:** Use direct DOM manipulation (`ref.current.style.transform`) instead of `useState` — avoids React re-renders on every mousemove.

### Glass effects on small elements
CSS classes with `::before`/`::after` pseudo-elements clip or overflow on small/circular elements (pills, filter tabs, timeline nodes). For these, use **inline styles** with `boxShadow: 'inset ...'` and `border: '1px solid rgba(...)'` instead.

## Build Pipeline (see `build-website` skill for details)
```
1. Analyze brief → Extract client colors, fonts, preferences, industry
2. ui-ux-pro-max → Data-driven design system (fills gaps the brief didn't specify)
3. style-archetypes → Detect archetype (8 available) → industry-tuned tool configurations
4. Merge layers → Client brief wins > archetype > ui-ux-pro-max
5. Design Blueprint → Map every tool's configuration (colors, speeds, densities, intensities)
6. Base44 Create → Project scaffold + deps + SEO meta
7. Build sections → section-templates for layout, premium-effects/scroll-kinetics/3d-scenes for atmosphere
8. Review & QA → Base + Enhancement quality, mobile audit, SEO check
9. Deploy → npm run build && npx base44 deploy
```

**NEVER skip review & QA. NEVER deploy without passing both.**
